<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870805-0062 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:TeleVideo Systems Inc.</HL><DD> 08/05/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS ZENT TELVTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   TeleVideo Systems Inc. said it signed a letter of intent to purchase all the shares outstanding of Zentec Corp. in an exchange of stock and cash currently valued at about $30.8 million. TeleVideo, a Sunnyvale, Calif.-based maker of computer terminals and workstations, said it would swap 8.7 million of its shares for all the common shares of Santa Clara, Calif.-based Zentec, which makes computer terminals. TeleVideo also will pay about $9 million for all of Zentec's preferred shares outstanding. The merger is subject to approval of both companies' shareholders and boards and the execution of a definitive agreement. Upon completion of the merger, K. Phillip Hwang, chairman of TeleVideo, will become chairman of the combined company, and William D. Parker, president of Zentec, will become president. </TEXT></DOC>